station-goal-shuttle = 
    Your shift's goal is to build a crewed shuttle in space and equip it with everything necessary for survival.
    To complete it, the supply department needs to order all necessary resources for the engineering and research departments.
    The engineering department needs to build it, and the research department must provide the engineering department and shuttle with all necessary equipment.
station-goal-solar-panels = 
    Your shift's goal is to organize a backup power system for the station based on solar panels.
    For this you will need to order all necessary materials from the supply department and then build 2 new solar panel arrays with the engineering department.
    Also ensure the isolation of the energy they produce in 3 new SMESes not connected to the station's main network.
station-goal-artifacts = 
    Your shift's goal is to find, research and deliver space artifacts.
    To complete it, you will need salvagers to search for and deliver artifacts from the debris around the station.
    After delivery, they must be handed over in a special container to the research department for study and documentation of their properties.
    You need to deliver at least 2 fully studied and documented artifacts to the evacuation shuttle in special containers.
    Recommended points for the artifact description document:
    - Name of the object
    - Description of the object's appearance
    - Properties of the object
    - Notes
    - Name and title of the responsible party
    The document must be certified with the seal of the chief researcher.
station-goal-bank = 
    Your shift's goal is to construct an orbital storage facility with supplies and technology.
    The storage facility should be placed in space separately from the main station, ensure the structural integrity of its construction, a stray meteor must not damage it.
    The storage facility should contain 4 boxes:
    - a box with advanced medicine
    - a box with supplies of the best seeds
    - a refrigerator box with high-nutrition food
    - a box with valuable but non-unique circuit boards
    Ensure the preservation of the contents in storage until the end of the shift.
station-goal-zoo = 
    Your shift's goal is to improve crew recreation on the station.
    The engineering department needs to build a zoo in close proximity to the dormitories with at least three enclosures of different animal species ordered from the supply department.
    Provide the animals with food, at least one cleaning robot in each enclosure, and everything necessary for survival depending on the animal species.
station-goal-mining-outpost = 
    Your shift's goal is to construct an orbital mining outpost for ore and resource extraction from asteroids.
    The outpost should be placed in space separately from the main station.
    Ensure structural integrity of its construction, a stray meteor must not damage it.
    The outpost should have the following:
    - autonomous, uninterruptible power source
    - gravity generator
    - equipment for performing work, particularly pickaxes, ore bags and 2 mining spacesuits
    - living quarters for 2 people, with atmosphere, lighting and windows
    - storage for mined resources and necessary food supplies
    - At least 500 units of beer and a refrigerator box with snacks
    - 4 sets of mechanical damage medicine

station-goal-tesla = 
    Your shift's goal is to build a generator based on a high-voltage Tesla coil.
    To complete it, the engineering department will need to build a containment cell, and the supply department will need to order all necessary materials.
    The containment cell must be capable of containing a Tesla body without the risk of destroying SMESSes.